      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "OBAT Helpers demonstrates a high level of organizational maturity through its <cite id=\"14\">Platinum Candid status</cite> and <cite id=\"2\">90.90.33333333333333/100 from Charity Navigator rating</cite>. Their governance is robust, featuring a <cite id=\"15\">22-member board</cite> that provides diverse oversight. This structural strength supports their <cite id=\"4\">direct service model</cite> in Bangladesh, where they manage <cite id=\"9\">3 health clinics</cite> and extensive WASH programs. Their ability to maintain <cite id=\"10\">5.7 months of working capital</cite> while keeping fundraising costs at just <cite id=\"7\">$0.06 per dollar</cite> highlights a lean and professional operation."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2004</cite>, OBAT Helpers Inc. focuses on lifting marginalized communities in Bangladesh out of poverty. The organization operates with a <cite id=\"2\">90.33/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting high standards of accountability. Their work centers on <cite id=\"3\">displaced and refugee communities</cite>, specifically targeting those in IDP camps and Rohingya refugees. OBAT provides a <cite id=\"4\">direct service delivery model</cite> that spans education, healthcare, and youth development. In 2023, the charity reported <cite id=\"5\">total revenue of $2,184,558</cite>. While they maintain a <cite id=\"6\">program expense ratio of 82.1%</cite>, they are exceptionally efficient in fundraising. They spend only <cite id=\"7\">$0.06 to raise every $1</cite>, which is well below industry averages. The organization manages <cite id=\"8\">50 educational and training projects</cite> and <cite id=\"9\">3 health clinics</cite> to provide consistent support to underserved populations. Their financial health is stable, maintaining <cite id=\"10\">5.7 months of working capital</cite> to ensure program continuity during funding fluctuations. As a <cite id=\"11\">zakat-eligible organization</cite>, OBAT allows Muslim donors to fulfill religious obligations by supporting the poor and needy (fuqara and masakin) through <cite id=\"12\">verified asnaf categories</cite>.",
